The paper discusses variable selection for regression with high-dimensional BIGDATA, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The use of L0 regularization and its comparison with L1 regularization (LASSO) is a topic of interest in the field of machine learning and statistics, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of an EM algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in computer science and statistics, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The application of the proposed method in bioinformatics and genomics suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the mention of theoretical properties and the use of cross-validation and AIC/BIC for parameter selection suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
